subtasks.details:
In Harpocrates/cli.py, find the scan command decorator. Change:
  @click.argument('path', type=click.Path(exists=True))
To:
  @click.argument('paths', nargs=-1, type=click.Path(exists=True, path_type=Path))

Update the function signature from `def scan(path, ...)` to `def scan(paths, ...)`.
Update loop inside to iterate: `for path in paths:`

In the per-file processing loop:
try:
    content = path.read_text(encoding='utf-8')
except UnicodeDecodeError:
    click.echo(f'[WARNING] Skipping binary/unreadable file: {path}', err=True)
    continue
except (OSError, PermissionError) as e:
    click.echo(f'[WARNING] Skipping unreadable file {path}: {e}', err=True)
    continue

Warning goes to stderr (err=True). The hook must NEVER crash on binary files.
